text: Diane E Lansley (married name White \- born 1953), is a female former swimmer who competed for England. ==Swimming career== She represented England and won a gold medal in the 100 metres butterfly and a silver medal in the 4 x 100 metres medley relay, at the 1970 British Commonwealth Games in Edinburgh, Scotland. ==References== Category:1953 births Category:English female swimmers Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in swimming Category:Commonwealth Games gold medallists for England Category:Commonwealth Games silver medallists for England Category:Swimmers at the 1970 British Commonwealth Games Category:Living people
